{"TopicId":188295,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Spacecraft that hop?","CreatedByName":"moogoob","CreatedById":118251,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-16T23:25:39Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"moogoob","CreatedById":118251,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-16T23:25:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo for some reason or another, I\u0027ve been spending some time playing around with Breaking Grounds\u0027 parts. And an idea hits me - what about using the pistons like a grasshopper\u0027s leg to get around on low-gravity worlds?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/Y_P7B5GcMTE?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s oddly effective, getting around Minmus at a fairly decent clip, even compared to wheels. Haven\u0027t tried it yet on higher-gravity worlds like the Mun (I\u0027d put way larger reaction wheels if I did).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs this something anybody else has tried? It just seems so bizarrely obvious. \u003Cspan\u003E:p \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-09-16T23:26:53Z\u0022 title=\u002209/16/2019 11:26  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 16, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by moogoob\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cavscout74","CreatedById":181783,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-17T00:29:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181256-klapaucius/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022181256\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181256-klapaucius/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Klapaucius\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E has of course already posted one hopper to Kerbalx:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Klapaucius/Aristophanes-the-Frog\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/Klapaucius/Aristophanes-the-Frog\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI seem to remember another one as well, but I can\u0027t find it as easily\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Klapaucius","CreatedById":181256,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-17T00:42:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223673261\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188295\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568680178\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181783\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cavscout74\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, Cavscout74 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181256-klapaucius/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022181256\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181256-klapaucius/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Klapaucius\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E has of course already posted one hopper to Kerbalx:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Klapaucius/Aristophanes-the-Frog\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/Klapaucius/Aristophanes-the-Frog\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI seem to remember another one as well, but I can\u0027t find it as easily\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/38787-klond/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002238787\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/38787-klond/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@klond\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0made a pogo stick.\u00A0 I don\u0027t think it is uploaded anywhere, but you can find it on page 2 of this challenge.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022153808\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6614958093\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/184892-breaking-ground-walker-speed-challenge/page/2/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:211px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223673237\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188295\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568676339\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022118251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022moogoob\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, moogoob said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo for some reason or another, I\u0027ve been spending some time playing around with Breaking Grounds\u0027 parts. And an idea hits me - what about using the pistons like a grasshopper\u0027s leg to get around on low-gravity worlds?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/Y_P7B5GcMTE?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s oddly effective, getting around Minmus at a fairly decent clip, even compared to wheels. Haven\u0027t tried it yet on higher-gravity worlds like the Mun (I\u0027d put way larger reaction wheels if I did).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs this something anybody else has tried? It just seems so bizarrely obvious. \u003Cspan\u003E:p \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI made this hydraulic to orbit craft. It only works on Gilly, however.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/IQ_nDJZ0mE4?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-17T00:46:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223673266\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188295\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568680921\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181256\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Klapaucius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Klapaucius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmade this hydraulic to orbit craft. It only works on Gilly, however.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do you keep it from hitting Gilly again at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E? I can\u0027t watch videos right now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"moogoob","CreatedById":118251,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-17T00:51:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223673266\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188295\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568680921\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181256\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Klapaucius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Klapaucius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI made this hydraulic to orbit craft. It only works on Gilly, however.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK that made me laugh. Haven\u0027t tried mine on Gilly; the 5-minute jumps would be agony.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223673268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188295\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568681187\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do you keep it from hitting Gilly again at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E? I can\u0027t watch videos right now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think he hit escape velocity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Klapaucius","CreatedById":181256,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-17T00:52:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223673268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188295\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568681187\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do you keep it from hitting Gilly again at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E? I can\u0027t watch videos right now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was not specific enough. It escapes Gilly and goes into orbit around Kerbol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tw1","CreatedById":59717,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-17T01:27:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve done something like this without the robotics before. It used strong reaction wheels to rock and bounce about over the surface with precision, as alternative to a rover.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ultimate Steve","CreatedById":161505,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-17T04:12:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly slightly related, but before bg I sent a tumbling rover called the tumbleweed to Gilly. It did not work well at all, it was a pain to get going and stop. It used reaction wheels and I beams to get around.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-09-17T04:12:37Z\u0022 title=\u002209/17/2019 04:12  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 17, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Ultimate Steve\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"N_Danger","CreatedById":159757,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-18T01:37:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Tumbled to a biome on Minmus once using a reaction wheel-\u00A0It was a long process, in a probe that ran out of fuel.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have never built a craft to do stuff like that on purpose but I am inspired now!\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}